# Bubblbook — production Stripe environment variables
# Copy to: scripts/bubblbook-production-stripe.env.local (gitignored)
# Then paste into Praxarch → Deployments → bubblbook → Configure → Production → env
#
# IMPORTANT: Do NOT reuse staging (alpha) values. Staging uses Stripe TEST mode
# (pk_test_…, sk_test_…). Production must use LIVE mode (pk_live_…, sk_live_…).
#
# Praxarch production vault today (compareServiceEnvKeys):
#   - stripe_key          → set (restricted key rk_live_… — verify this is still valid)
#   - stripe_pb_key       → MISSING
#   - stripe_subscription_prod_id → MISSING
#   - stripe_subscription_price_id → MISSING
#   - stripe_wh_key       → MISSING
#   - stripe_wh_signing_secret → MISSING
#
# ── Where to get LIVE values ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. https://dashboard.stripe.com — toggle "Test mode" OFF (live mode)
# 2. Developers → API keys
#      stripe_pb_key  = Publishable key (pk_live_…)
#      stripe_key     = Secret key (sk_live_…) OR restricted key (rk_live_…) with needed scopes
# 3. Products → your subscription product
#      stripe_subscription_prod_id  = Product ID (prod_…)
#      stripe_subscription_price_id = Price ID (price_…)
#    Use LIVE product/price IDs — test IDs from alpha will not work in production.
# 4. Developers → Webhooks → endpoint for https://bubblbook.com (or your prod API path)
#      stripe_wh_signing_secret = Signing secret (whsec_…) for the LIVE webhook endpoint
#      stripe_wh_key            = Often the same whsec_… (match what Bubblbook app expects)
#
# If the site already charged customers under PM2, copy LIVE values from the legacy
# server .env on 34.251.139.131 before rotating keys in Stripe.
#
# ── Fill in below, then import via Praxarch setServiceEnvVars (merge: true) ─

stripe_pb_key=
stripe_key=
stripe_subscription_prod_id=
stripe_subscription_price_id=
stripe_wh_key=
stripe_wh_signing_secret=
